SSL-TSL

### Certificate Verification

```bash # Check certificate expiration date sudo openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/hostname.crt -noout -dates

# Verify certificate Subject Alternative Names (SANs) sudo openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/hostname.crt -text -noout | grep -A1 “Subject Alternative Name”

# Check certificate issuer sudo openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/hostname.crt -noout -issuer

# View full certificate details sudo openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/hostname.crt -text -noout

# Test HTTPS connection curl -v https://service.lab.local

# Test SSL/TLS handshake openssl s_client -connect service.lab.local:443 -servername service.lab.local ```

### HTTP to HTTPS Redirect Testing

```bash # Test redirect curl -I http://service.lab.local

# Should show: # HTTP/1.1 301 Moved Permanently # Location: https://service.lab.local/

# Follow redirect automatically curl -L http://service.lab.local ```

### Nginx SSL Configuration

```bash # Test nginx configuration docker exec nginx nginx -t

# View SSL configuration docker exec nginx cat /etc/nginx/nginx.conf | grep -A 10 “ssl”

# Check if SSL directory is mounted docker exec nginx ls -la /etc/nginx/ssl/

# Reload nginx (for config changes) docker compose restart nginx

# Recreate nginx (for volume changes) docker compose down nginx && docker compose up -d nginx ```

### FreeIPA CA Certificate

```bash # Download FreeIPA CA certificate curl -o ~/ipa-ca.crt http://mgmt.lab.local/ipa/config/ca.crt

# View CA certificate details openssl x509 -in ~/ipa-ca.crt -text -noout

# Install CA certificate on Linux sudo cp ~/ipa-ca.crt /usr/local/share/ca-certificates/ sudo update-ca-trust ```

